---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title="About" description="About the evolutionaryABM research group." />
    <style>
      main { max-width: 860px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
      h1 { font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; color: #111; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
      .card { border: 1px solid #eee; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
      .card h2 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #111; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
      .card p { font-size: 0.9rem; color: #555; line-height: 1.75; }
      .tags { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; margin-top: 1rem; }
      .tag { font-size: 12px; background: #f5f5f5; color: #555; padding: 4px 10px; border-radius: 20px; border: 1px solid #eee; }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <h1>About</h1>
      <div class="card">
        <h2>Our mission</h2>
        <p>We investigate how complex adaptive behaviors emerge from simple rules — whether in biological cells, animal populations, or human political systems. Agent-based modeling lets us simulate these systems and test hypotheses that are difficult to study empirically.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h2>Approach</h2>
        <p>Each project combines computational simulation with domain theory. We build models in Java using MASON and Repast, ground them in empirical data, and share findings openly. All code is available on GitHub.</p>
        <div class="tags">
          <span class="tag">Agent-based modeling</span>
          <span class="tag">Evolutionary dynamics</span>
          <span class="tag">Complex systems</span>
          <span class="tag">Computational social science</span>
          <span class="tag">Systems biology</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h2>Affiliation</h2>
        <p>Based at Purdue University, West Lafayette, Indiana.</p>
      </div>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>
